AI-Powered Legal Document Review System (Multi-Agent Architecture)
1. 📌 Overview
1.1 Purpose

The system automates legal document analysis using a multi-agent AI pipeline, leveraging Azure OpenAI and a legal knowledge base to:

Extract clauses
Validate compliance
Assess risk
Generate executive summaries
Produce a final legal verdict
1.2 Key Objectives
Reduce manual legal review effort
Ensure regulatory compliance (GDPR, HIPAA, SOX, etc.)
Provide explainable AI-driven insights
Enable scalable legal analysis
2. 🧩 System Architecture
2.1 High-Level Architecture Diagram
+----------------------+
|      User (CLI)      |
+----------+-----------+
           |
           v
+-----------------------------+
|     Orchestrator Layer      |
|  (Main Async Controller)    |
+-------------+---------------+
              |
   -----------------------------------------
   |         |            |                |
   v         v            v                v
+--------+ +-------------+ +-------------+ +------------------+
| Agent1 | |  Agent2     | |  Agent3     | |   Agent4         |
| Ingest | | Clause Ext. | | Compliance  | | Summary Agent    |
+--------+ +-------------+ +-------------+ +------------------+
     |           |               |                 |
     |           |               |                 |
     v           v               v                 v
 Local File   Azure OpenAI   Azure OpenAI    Azure OpenAI
              + Grounding    + Grounding     + Grounding
                     \           |                /
                      \          |               /
                       ----------+---------------
                                  |
                                  v
                        +-------------------+
                        | Final Report Gen  |
                        | (Orchestrator AI) |
                        +-------------------+
                                  |
                                  v
                        +-------------------+
                        |  Output + Risk    |
                        |  Dashboard        |
                        +-------------------+
2.2 Component Breakdown
Component	Description
User Interface (CLI)	Accepts document path
Orchestrator Agent	Controls end-to-end workflow
Document Ingestion Agent	Reads legal document
Clause Extraction Agent	Extracts structured clauses
Compliance Validation Agent	Validates against regulations
Grounded Summary Agent	Generates executive summary
Azure OpenAI	LLM processing engine
Knowledge Base (RAG)	legaldoc_grounding.txt
Risk Dashboard	Displays risk metrics
3. 🔄 Sequence Diagram
User
 |
 | Enter Document Path
 v
Orchestrator
 |
 |----> Document Ingestion Agent
 |         |
 |         | Read File
 |         v
 |     Document Text
 |
 |----> Clause Extraction Agent
 |         |
 |         | (LLM + Grounding)
 |         v
 |     Extracted Clauses (JSON)
 |
 |----> Compliance Validation Agent
 |         |
 |         | (LLM + Regulations)
 |         v
 |     Compliance Report
 |
 |----> Summary Agent
 |         |
 |         | (LLM + Context)
 |         v
 |     Executive Summary
 |
 |----> Orchestrator AI
 |         |
 |         | Combine all outputs
 |         v
 |     Final Legal Report
 |
 v
User (Output + Risk Dashboard)
4. 🧠 Multi-Agent Design Pattern
4.1 Agent Responsibilities
Agent	Responsibility
Agent 1	Data ingestion
Agent 2	NLP + clause structuring
Agent 3	Compliance reasoning
Agent 4	Business summarization
Orchestrator	Decision-making & synthesis
4.2 Design Pattern Used
Orchestrator Pattern (Centralized Control)
RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation)
Pipeline Processing
LLM-as-a-Service Architecture
5. 📊 Data Flow
Raw Document
     ↓
Text Extraction
     ↓
Clause JSON
     ↓
Compliance Report
     ↓
Executive Summary
     ↓
Final Consolidated Report
6. 📚 Business Use Cases
6.1 Primary Use Cases
✅ Use Case 1: Legal Contract Review
Upload contract
Extract clauses
Identify risky terms
Get compliance status
✅ Use Case 2: Regulatory Compliance Audit
Validate document against:
GDPR
HIPAA
SOX
Highlight violations
✅ Use Case 3: Risk Assessment
Compute risk score (0–100)
Identify critical issues
Trigger escalation if >70
✅ Use Case 4: Executive Reporting
Generate summary for:
Legal heads
Business stakeholders
Provide actionable insights
✅ Use Case 5: Pre-Signing Contract Validation
Analyze before approval
Suggest corrections
Provide verdict:
APPROVED
NEEDS REVISION
REJECTED
7. 🧾 Functional Requirements
Upload legal document (local file)
Extract structured clauses
Perform compliance validation
Generate executive summary
Produce final legal verdict
Display risk dashboard
8. ⚙️ Non-Functional Requirements
Category	Requirement
Performance	Async processing for scalability
Security	API key protection, secure endpoints
Scalability	Multi-agent parallelizable design
Reliability	Error handling via try/catch
Maintainability	Modular agent-based architecture
Observability	Logging at each stage
9. 🔐 Security Considerations
API key should be stored securely (NOT hardcoded)
Sensitive legal data handling
Role-based access (future enhancement)
Encryption for data at rest/in transit
10. ⚠️ Risks & Limitations
LLM hallucination risk
Dependency on grounding quality
Regulatory updates require KB updates
Large documents may hit token limitsAI-Powered Legal Document Review System (Multi-Agent Architecture)
